        <h2 id="directions">Directions</h2>
        
        
        <p class="step"><strong>Step 1:</strong> While waiting for the pasta, start to repare the sauce. <strong>Make sure that the spagehetti will be hot enough when the sauce is finished</strong>. The pasta need to be hot enough to cook the raw eggs in the sauce.
</p>
<p class="step"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Boil salted water in a large pot. Cook the past around 8 to 10 minutes, or until the pasta is tnder yet still firm. After that, drain the pasta. Reserving 1/2 cup of starchy cooking water to use in the sauce (optional)
<p class="step"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Meanwhile, start heating up the olive oil in a deep  skillet over <strong>medium heat</strong>. Add the pancetta and saute for about 3 mins, until the bacon is crisp and the fat is redenered. Toss the garlic into the fat and saute for less than 1 minutes.
</p>
<p class="step"><strong>Step 4:</strong> Add the spaghetti into the pan and toss for 2 minutes to coat the starnds with bacon fat. Mix the Parmesan and eggs together in a seperate bowl, stril until there're no lumps. emove the pan from the heat. Use the starchy cooking water to thin out the sauce until it reaches the desired consistency. Add in some grounded black pepper. Put the spaghetti onto the plate and top it off with some freshly chopped parely.
</p>
</p>
   



        
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.foodnetwork.com/recipes/tyler-florence/spaghetti-alla-carbonara-recipe-1914140">Recipe #1 website</a></em></p>
